cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with open source software development and the identification of paid and unpaid developers. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the implications of the transferability of research results to closed source software industry. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper uses code source repository meta-data to build a dataset of active developers. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to open source development. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also less likely but possible as the paper uses machine learning techniques to predict paid and unpaid open source development.
